            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Here are the latest service updates for the London Underground:\n\n1. **Service Disruptions**: On December 6 and 7, there will be no service on the Piccadilly Line between Acton Town and Uxbridge, and no service on the Metropolitan Line between Harrow-on-the-Hill and Uxbridge. Replacement bus services will be available [TfL Updates](https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?dateTypeSelect%3DThis%20weekend).\n\n2. **Festive Period Changes**: Most public transport services will not operate on Christmas Day, and significant closures are expected on Boxing Day, including the Elizabeth Line. Services will run early on Christmas Eve and for New Year's Eve, but may stop at short notice to manage crowds [TfL Updates](https://tfl.gov.uk/status-updates/major-works-and-events/christmas-and-new-year-travel).\n\nYou can check detailed updates and plan your journey using the [TfL website](https://tfl.gov.uk/).",
